info.senderName: NWS Baltimore/Washington (Washington D.C., Central Maryland, Northern Virginia, Eastern West Virginia)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued June 05 at 10:55AM EDT until June 05 at 3:00PM EDT by NWS Baltimore/Washington
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM EDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Up to one half foot of inundation above ground level in low lying areas due to tidal flooding. * WHERE...Shoreline in Cecil County. * WHEN...Until 3 PM EDT this afternoon, especially around the time of high tide. * IMPACTS...At 4.5 feet, minor shoreline flooding begins near Charlestown. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Tides one and a half to two feet above normal. The next high tide at Chesapeake City is at 12:06 PM and 12:39 AM. The next high tide at Port Deposit is at 11:34 AM and 12:03 AM. The next high tide at Charlestown is at 12:02 PM and 12:31 AM.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
